{"parse":{"title":"Air Transportation Stabilization Board","pageid":2304457,"revid":815547768,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Air Transportation Stabilization Board</b> (ATSB) is an office of <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Department_of_the_Treasury\" title=\"United States Department of the Treasury\">United States Department of the Treasury</a> created to assist <a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">US</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Airline\" title=\"Airline\">airlines</a> in the wake of the <a href=\"/wiki/September_11,_2001_attacks\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"September 11, 2001 attacks\">September 11, 2001 attacks</a>.\n</p><p>The Air Transportation Safety and System Stabilization Act, signed into law September 22, 2001, authorizes the board to issue up to $10 billion in federal loan guarantees to air carriers for which credit is not otherwise available and where \"such agreement is a necessary part of maintaining a safe, efficient and viable commercial aviation system in the United States.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Loan_guarantees\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Loan guarantees</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#ATSB_Results\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">ATSB Results</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Successes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Successes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Still_in_Business_and_holding_on_in_life_support\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Still in Business and holding on in life support</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Casualties\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Casualties</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Loan_guarantees\">Loan guarantees</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_Transportation_Stabilization_Board&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Loan guarantees\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Between 2001 and 2003, the ATSB approved applications for loan guarantees from seven carriers: <a href=\"/wiki/America_West_Airlines\" title=\"America West Airlines\">America West Airlines</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/US_Airways\" title=\"US Airways\">US Airways</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/American_Trans_Air\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"American Trans Air\">American Trans Air</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Aloha_Airlines\" title=\"Aloha Airlines\">Aloha Airlines</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Frontier_Airlines\" title=\"Frontier Airlines\">Frontier Airlines</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Evergreen_International_Airlines\" title=\"Evergreen International Airlines\">Evergreen International Airlines</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/World_Airways\" title=\"World Airways\">World Airways</a>. These carriers accepted loan guarantees worth $1.179 billion.\n</p><p>The ATSB denied applications from nine carriers: Ozark Airlines dba <a href=\"/wiki/Great_Plains_Airlines\" title=\"Great Plains Airlines\">Great Plains Airlines</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=MEDjet_International&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"MEDjet International (page does not exist)\">MEDjet International</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Corporate_Airlines\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Corporate Airlines\">Corporate Airlines</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Gemini_Air_Cargo\" title=\"Gemini Air Cargo\">Gemini Air Cargo</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Frontier_Flying_Service\" title=\"Frontier Flying Service\">Frontier Flying Service</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Spirit_Airlines\" title=\"Spirit Airlines\">Spirit Airlines</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/National_Airlines_(N7)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"National Airlines (N7)\">National Airlines</a>, and both initial and revised applications from <a href=\"/wiki/United_Airlines\" title=\"United Airlines\">United Airlines</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Vanguard_Airlines\" title=\"Vanguard Airlines\">Vanguard Airlines</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"ATSB_Results\">ATSB Results</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_Transportation_Stabilization_Board&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: ATSB Results\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Successes\">Successes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_Transportation_Stabilization_Board&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Successes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><b>America West Airlines</b> - ceases to exist, merges with US Airways under the <a href=\"/wiki/US_Airways_Group\" title=\"US Airways Group\">US Airways Group</a> umbrella.</li>\n<li><b>US Airways</b> - merges with America West to form US Airways</li></ul>\n<dl><dd>Additionally with this merger, US Airways survived long enough to merge yet again, into and with <a href=\"/wiki/American_Airlines_Group\" title=\"American Airlines Group\">American Airlines Group</a> thus becoming; <a href=\"/wiki/American_Airlines\" title=\"American Airlines\">American Airlines</a>.</dd></dl>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Still_in_Business_and_holding_on_in_life_support\">Still in Business and holding on in life support</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_Transportation_Stabilization_Board&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Still in Business and holding on in life support\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><b>Frontier Airlines</b> - reorganizes after a chapter 11 bankruptcy filing and is acquired by <a href=\"/wiki/Republic_Airways_Holdings\" title=\"Republic Airways Holdings\">Republic Airways Holdings</a> and then the private investment group Indigo Partners.</li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Casualties\">Casualties</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_Transportation_Stabilization_Board&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Casualties\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><b>Aloha Airlines</b> - shut down in a chapter 7 bankruptcy filing.</li>\n<li><b>American Trans Air</b> - acquired by the private equity firm <a href=\"/wiki/MatlinPatterson\" title=\"MatlinPatterson\">MatlinPatterson's</a> Global Aero Logistics and shut down in chapter 7 bankruptcy filing.</li>\n<li><b>Evergreen International Airlines</b></li>\n<li><b>World Airways</b> - acquired by the same group as <a href=\"/wiki/American_Trans_Air\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"American Trans Air\">ATA</a> and also shut down by the same private equity firm</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_Transportation_Stabilization_Board&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">ATSB Loan Guarantees,<cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20080220134114/http://www.treas.gov/offices/domestic-finance/atsb/loan-guarantees.shtml\">\"Archived copy\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.treas.gov/offices/domestic-finance/atsb/loan-guarantees.shtml\">the original</a> on 2008-02-20<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-02-26</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Archived+copy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.treas.gov%2Foffices%2Fdomestic-finance%2Fatsb%2Floan-guarantees.shtml&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAir+Transportation+Stabilization+Board\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> </span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_Transportation_Stabilization_Board&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>U.S. Treasury - Air Transportation Stabilization Board<cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20100811172746/http://www.treas.gov/offices/domestic-finance/atsb/\">\"Archived copy\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external t